Git secrets

## Repositories
### Connect to a newly made remote repository
cd where-you-want-it-to-go (e.g., cd ..)
git clone https://github.com/annam21/newrepo
### Switch repositories
cd reponame

## Branches
### Switch branches
git checkout branchname
### Create a new branch and switch to it
git checkout -b newbranchname
### Connect new branch to remote
git push -u origin newbranchname
### Delete a branch locally
git branch -d branchname
### Delete remote branch
git push origin --delete branchname
### See all branches
git branch -a (list)
git show-branch (tree)

### Install a package from a branch
devtools::install_github("ananm21/spaceNtime@branchname")

## Version numbers
### How to on git
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45061918/versioning-an-r-package-with-git-github
### Standards for what number it is
http://r-pkgs.had.co.nz/release.html
### Tag your commit
git tag 0.0.1
### Push commits
git push
### Push tags
git push --tags
### Now someone's supposed to be able to access this by
install_github("annam21/spaceNtime@0.0.1")

## Update git 
### check version 
git version
### update
git update-git-for-windows

## Initial commit 
(Check working directory)
git add .
git commit "initial commit"
(Create github repository online)
git remote add origin https://github.com/annam21/repo-name
git push -u origin master 